==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reddendum
<hw>Red*den"dum</hw> <pr>(r?d*d?n"d?m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Neut. of L. <ets>reddendus</ets> that must be given back or
yielded, gerundive of <ets>reddere</ets>. See <er>Reddition</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A clause in a deed by which some new thing is
reserved out of what had been granted before; the clause by which rent
is reserved in a lease.</def> <rj><au>Cruise.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reddish</ent>⟦br⟧
